# «.Name»

A gsx + Vite starter (server-rendered HTML, live reload in dev, hashed assets in prod).

## Prerequisites
- Go 1.24+
- Node 18+ (npm)
- [Task](https://taskfile.dev) (`task`)

## Setup
```sh
go get -tool github.com/gsxhq/gsx/cmd/gsx@latest
go mod tidy
npm install
```

## Develop
```sh
task dev
```
Open http://localhost:5173. Edit `app.gsx` and save — the browser live-reloads.

## Production build
```sh
npm run build   # vite build → dist/ (hashed assets + manifest)
go build -o app # embeds dist/, serves /static/, reads the manifest
./app           # serves on :7777 with no Vite process
```

## How it works
- The Vite plugin watches `.gsx` and runs `go tool gsx generate`; `wgo` rebuilds
  and restarts the Go server; the server POSTs Vite `/__reload` after boot.
- `main.go` builds a `*vite.Vite` from `VITE_DEV_URL` and injects it into each
  request via `v.Middleware`; `app.gsx` reads the asset bundle from the context.
